OL,3,CMP responds after concerns district
OL,4,Ccouncil could switch counties
OL,6,F"There are not going to be two
OL,7,Fcouncils anymore, just one council.
OL,9,F"Exactly what it looks like locally we
OL,10,Fdon't yet know - this might mean that
OL,11,Fpart or whole of the constituencies
OL,12,Fmoves in with one of the cities, or we
OL,13,Fend up as a rural council, or (parts
OL,14,Fof Erewash) could end up in multiple
OL,15,Fdifferent councils - everything is on
OL,16,Fthe table."
OL,18,FPeople in Long Eaton were mostly
OL,19,Fagainst the idea of Erewash becoming
OL,20,Fpart of Nottinghamshire.
